IN THE ARBITRAL PROCEEDINGS

M/s. Rajasthan Construction Consortium          ...Claimant 
VERSUS
Water Resources Department, Govt. of Rajasthan  ...Respondent

STATEMENT OF CLAIM
TOTAL CLAIM: ₹54.85 Crore + 12% Interest

=========================
CLAIM 1: UNFORESEEN GEOLOGICAL CONDITIONS – ₹18.75 Crore
Facts: The tender indicated soil and weathered rock. At 8m depth, massive un-weathered basalt and swelling clay were struck.
Clause Relied: FIDIC Sub-Clause 4.12 (Unforeseeable Physical Conditions).
Evidence: Geotech expert report, drilling logs, differential rate analysis for hard rock blasting.

CLAIM 2: DESIGN CHANGE BY DEPARTMENT – ₹12.60 Crore
Facts: The spillway capacity requirement was increased midway due to new CWC guidelines. This fundamentally altered the design and resulted in redundant concrete demolition.
Clause Relied: FIDIC Clause 13.1.
Evidence: Revised drawings stamped by CE.

CLAIM 3: DELAY IN MATERIAL APPROVAL – ₹7.85 Crore
Facts: Geotextile and specialized cement approvals held up by the design directorate for 140 days.

CLAIM 4: IDLE PLANT & MACHINERY – ₹9.40 Crore
Facts: Shuttering gear, batching plant, excavators idle during design limbo.

CLAIM 5: LOSS OF PROFIT – ₹6.25 Crore

PRAYER
Award ₹54.85 Crore + interest, and set aside the wrongful termination order.
Date: 15.04.2026
